LORE rakuen-clerk
FLAGS RAKUEN CLERK
Garden Ledger Clerks maintain the shadow archive of names transferred to
the Conclave via "resettled south" mechanisms during the Violet Compact era;
the Bloom Council accepted this; the Clerks have not forgiven it
The Southward Compact founding document has been edited; later editions
removed sections most critical of Midgaard's registry culture; the Clerks
maintain the original
Dunnmark Letters (founder Caitha Dunnmark's correspondence) are in the Clerk
archives; they show a founder who expected the paradise model to fail; the
Bloom Council does not publicize this
Public accounting of food, water, and labor is a Compact requirement; the
Clerks actually implement it and survive Bloom Council tenure rotations
Three refused petitions are fully documented; the Clerks know exactly what
Midgaard's stated objections were and why they were politically motivated
~
